text.section:
A person granted an industrial hemp grower license shall:
Maintain records that reflect compliance with KRS 260.850 to 260.869, and with all other state laws regulating the planting and cultivation of industrial hemp;
Retain all industrial hemp production records for at least three (3) years;
Allow industrial hemp crops, throughout sowing, growing, and harvesting, to be inspected by and at the discretion of the commission or its designees, and the Department of Kentucky State Police and other law enforcement officers;
File with the commission documentation indicating that the industrial hemp seeds planted were of a type and variety certified to have no more THC concentration than that adopted by federal law in the Controlled Substances Act, 21 U.S.C. secs. 801 et seq.;
Notify the commission of the sale of any industrial hemp grown under the license and the names and addresses of the persons to whom the industrial hemp was sold; and
Provide the commission with copies of any contracts between the licensee and any person to whom industrial hemp was sold.
